## Code Style

- Use early returns to reduce nesting
- Comments only when crucial for context (lowercase). Avoid inline comments; use only when needed.

## Naming

- Event handlers: `handleClick`, `handleKeyDown`, `handleSubmit`
- Arrow functions with types: `const toggle = (): void => {}`

## Styling

- Tailwind classes only, no CSS files or `<style>` tags. Use CSS only when strictly needed.
- Use `cn()` from utils for conditional classes

## Accessibility

- Interactive elements need: `tabIndex={0}`, `aria-label`, keyboard handlers
- Semantic HTML: `<button>` for actions, `<a>` for navigation
